<paragraph blockId="19.[225,1437,1228,1376]" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">
Genus of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2001" box="[459,595,1228,1254]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="19" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Taouzitidae</taxonomicName>
with extremely discoidal, subinvolute to involute conch; venter subacute or acute in the adult stage. With single ventrolateral grooves. Suture line with wide external lobe, high median saddle, V-shaped E2 lobe, V-shaped lateral lobe and shallow, rounded umbilical lobes. Suture line formula (E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[406,415,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">2</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[440,449,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">1</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[474,483,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">2</subScript>
) L U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[545,554,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">2</subScript>
U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[582,591,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">4</subScript>
: U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[627,636,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">3</subScript>
U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[664,673,1362,1376]" fontSize="6" pageId="19" pageNumber="29">1</subScript>
I.
</paragraph>
